name: December 24th - Supper's Ready
description:
Since I am Neapolitan, it's a tradition to prepare fried large eel for the Christmas Eve dinner. These are the hands of my beloved aunt Maria while she's cleaning the fish before the final cooking process. To be honest, I wanted to shoot a lot more pictures during these "family days" but this photo, in particular, made me feel like I had already captured the sense of what these holidays represent to me -
5702 ×3803 px - Totally printable Digital Photo - Shoot in Fontana Nuova, Italy
